                                                                                                                       7                                      ICC meeting to discuss FTP, DRS
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Future Tours Programme (FTP) from the year 2012 to 2020 and the controversial Decision Review System (DRS) will top the agenda when the ICC Chief Executives Committee meets in Cape Town on Monday.         
	The ICC Chief Executives Committee (CEC) will convene in Cape Town tomorrow (Monday) for the third of its four meetings in 2010, the ICC said in a statement.         
	The CEC, to be chaired by ICC chief executive Haroon Lorgat, will consider a proposal from its working group on introducing context for international cricket with the view to confirming the FTP from 2012 to 2020.         
	The proposal will include the possibility of Test and ODI leagues as well as that of a Test play-off, the ICC said.                                                                                                                     
